{"build_type":"executable","description":"PT_INTERP loader (3c). Compiled as a position-independent interpreter; a thin binary names it in its PT_INTERP header so the kernel invokes it. It reads AT_EXECFN from the auxiliary vector (the path of the thin binary being run), reads the sidecar manifest at <execfn>.manifest = {\"libdir\":..,\"entry\":..}, then delegates to link_closure_and_invoke_entry to load and link the entry's object closure by name and run it. The entry's result becomes the process exit code (via the _start stub), so no kernel-stack reconstruction is needed: our programs are function closures the loader calls directly. [PATCH 2026-06-28: prepend mmap+endow-calling-thread-with-private-arena so the loader establishes FS/arena BEFORE any FS-relative global access — makes the loader correct regardless of static-vs-%fs global lowering (deterministic fix for the broken-loader regression)] [2026-07-04: rebuilt as no-interp static ET_EXEC for direct-exec relocatability]","module_name":"execute-compact-binary-originating-matching-manifest","package_name":"execute-compact-binary-originating-matching-manifest","function_definitions":{"execute-compact-binary-originating-matching-manifest":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"__lz","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"__lsix","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":6},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"__lprot","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"__lflags","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":34},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration",